{
  "title": "Politics vs Technology",
  "text": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "2 Jan 94"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "From: Mike Ingle > But"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "could the government ban a"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "book today? Of course not,"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "at least not"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "after one person typed it"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "or scanned it into a"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "computer. Technological gains are permanent."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The political approach is only"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "useful as a tactical weapon,"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "to hold them off until"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "technological solutions are in place."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If you want to change"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "the world, don't protest. Write"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "code!"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "This position seems to be"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "fast becoming cypherpunks dogma, but"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "I don't agree.  The"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "notion that we can just"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "fade into cypherspace and ignore"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "the unpleasant political realities is"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "unrealistic, in my view."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Have people forgotten the Clipper"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "proposal, with the possible follow-on"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "to make non-Clipper encryption illegal?"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": " To the extent this"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "proposal has been or will"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "be defeated, it will happen"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "through political maneuvering, not technology."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Have people forgotten the PGP"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "export investigation?  Phil Zimmermann"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "hasn't. He and others may"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "be facing the prospect of"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "ten years in prison if"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "they were found guilty of"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "illegal export.  If anyone"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "has any suggestions for how"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "to escape from jail into"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "cyberspace I'd like to hear"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "about them."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Mike's SecureDrive is a terrific"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "program for protecting privacy. "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "But if we want to"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "keep keys secret from politically-motivated"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "investigations, we have to rely"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "on the very political and"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "non-technological Fifth Amendment (an amendment"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "which Mike Godwin of EFF"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "and others contend does not"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "actually protect disclosure of cryptographic"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "keys).  Again, we need"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "to win political, not technological,"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "victories in order to protect"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "our privacy."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "I even question Mike's point"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "about the government's inability to"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "ban books. Look at the"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "difficulty in keeping PGP available"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "in this country even though"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "it is legal.  Not"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "only have FTP sites been"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "steadily closed down, even the"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "key servers have as well."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": " And this is legal"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "software.  "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Sure, this software is currently"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "available overseas, but that is"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "because PGP's only legal limitations"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "are the U.S. patent issues."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": " Imagine how much worse"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "it would be if non-escrowed"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "encryption were made illegal in"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "a broad range of countries,"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "with stringent limits on net"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "access to countries which promote"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "illegal software?  Here again,"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "these kinds of decisions will"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "be made in the political"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "realm."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Fundamentally, I believe we will"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "have the kind of society"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "that most people want. "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If we want freedom and"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "privacy, we must persuade others"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "that these are worth having."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": " There are no shortcuts."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": " Withdrawing into technology is"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "like pulling the blankets over"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "your head.  It feels"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "good for a while, until"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "reality catches up.  The"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "next Clipper or Digital Telephony"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "proposal will provide a rude"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "awakening."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Hal Finney   hal@rain.org"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": " "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "[Hal Finney Home Page](home.html)"
    }
  ]
}
